# Temporal v1.29.4 → v1.31.0 Upgrade Notes
#
# This manifest set deploys Temporal v1.29.4 with PostgreSQL.
# Below is a summary of what needs to change for the upgrade.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# UPGRADE CHECKLIST: v1.29.4 → v1.30.x → v1.31.0
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# STEP 1: v1.29.4 → v1.30.x
#   - Update image tags: temporalio/server:1.30.x, temporalio/admin-tools:1.30.x
#   - No schema changes required
#   - Note: docker image slimmed down (tctl, dockerize, curl removed)
#
# STEP 2: v1.30.x → v1.31.0
#   ⚠️ MANDATORY SCHEMA UPGRADES:
#   - PostgreSQL core: upgrade to schema v1.19
#   - PostgreSQL visibility: upgrade to schema v1.14
#     (also Elasticsearch v14 if using ES)
#
#   - Update image tags: temporalio/server:1.31.0, temporalio/admin-tools:1.31.0
#   - Schema Job: add a new job to run schema upgrades
#   - Dynamic Config: add new flags (system.enablePrincipalAttribution, etc.)
#   - New table: current_chasm_executions (created by schema migration)
#
# BREAKING CHANGES in v1.31.0:
#   - Worker Versioning V1/V2 APIs removed in next version (v1.32.0)
#   - Nexus always enabled (feature flag removed)
#   - Custom persistence: must add ArchetypeID support
#   - New matcher enabled by default (priority keys now respected)
#
# NEW FEATURES (off by default):
#   - system.enablePrincipalAttribution → true (Principal attribution)
#   - activity.enableStandalone → true (Standalone Activities)
#   - passwordCommand config for IAM-based SQL auth
#   - Cassandra 5.0.4+ support